%N A183623 Number of (n+1) X (n+1) 0..2 arrays with every 2 X 2 subblock summing to 4.
%H A183623 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A183623/b183623.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a>
%H A183623 Christian Krause, <a href="/A183623/a183623.txt">Proof of formula</a>, Jun 19 2026
%H A183623 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (10,-35,50,-24).
%F A183623 a(n) = (2^(n+1)-2)^2+2*3^(n+1)-3 = 4*4^n+6*3^n-8*2^n+1. - _Zhuorui He_, Jun 13 2026
%F A183623 From _Stefano Spezia_, Jun 21 2026: (Start)
%F A183623 G.f.: x*(19 - 103*x + 150*x^2 - 72*x^3)/((1 - x)*(1 - 2*x)*(1 - 3*x)*(1 - 4*x)).
%F A183623 E.g.f.: 4*exp(4*x) + 6*exp(3*x) - 8*exp(2*x) + exp(x) - 3. (End)
%e A183623 Some solutions for 3 X 3:
%e A183623 ..1..2..0....0..2..0....1..2..0....2..0..1....1..1..0....0..1..0....0..1..1
%e A183623 ..0..1..1....2..0..2....1..0..2....0..2..1....0..2..1....1..2..1....2..1..1
%e A183623 ..2..1..1....1..1..1....2..1..1....2..0..1....1..1..0....0..1..0....1..0..2
%t A183623 A183623[n_] := 4*4^n + 6*3^n - 8*2^n + 1;
%t A183623 Array[A183623, 25] (* _Paolo Xausa_, Jun 22 2026 *)
